  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Syria Floods 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heavy rains starting on 31 March has resulted in serious flooding in the Al Hasakeh Governorate of Syria leaving 235 000 people affected in towns and villages in the North East of Syria. Many are living in camps for people internally displaced displaced because of recent military activity. Serious damage to homes and agricultural lands has been reported in Quamishli Jawadiyeh Ta robiyah Tal Hamis Qahtaniyyeh Al Hasakeh and the IDP camp in Areesheh as well as IDP Al Hol Camp. BRC will support SARC on the emergency flood response through Protection Shelter and PMEAL Number of beneficiaries: Protection: 25 000 individuals Shelter: 5 000 individuals PMEAL: SARC staff and volunteers/All RC Movement will be benefited from the PMEAL components of the project</narrative>
  </description>
